frisch.title: Frisch elasticity of labor supply
frisch.notes: See Altonji (JPE, 1986) and Peterman (Econ Inquiry, 2016) for estimates of the Frisch elasticity.

g_y_annual.title: Exogenous growth rate of labor augmenting technological change
g_y_annual.description: Growth rate of labor augmenting technological change.

S.title: Maximum number of periods of economic life of model agent
S.description: Maximum number of periods of economic life of model agent.

J.title: Number of different labor productivity types of agents
J.description: Number of different labor productivity types of agents.

T.title: Number of periods until it is assumed that the model reaches its steady state
T.description: Number of periods until it is assumed that the model reaches its steady state.

lambdas.title: Fraction of population of each labor productivity type
lambdas.description: Fraction of population of each labor productivity type.

starting_age.title: Age at which households become economically active
starting_age.description: Age at which households become economically active.

ending_age.title: Maximum age a household can live until
ending_age.description: Maximum age a household can live until.

constant_demographics.title: Use constant demographics
constant_demographics.notes: This boolean allows one to use empirical mortality rates, but keep the population distribution constant across periods.  Note that immigration is shut off when this is true.

beta_annual.title: Annual rate of time preference for households
beta_annual.description: Annual rate of time preference for households.
beta_annual.notes: Default value from Carroll (JME, 2009).  Allows for each type to have a different value.

sigma.title: Coefficient of relative risk aversion in household utility function
sigma.description: Coefficient of relative risk aversion in household utility function.
sigma.notes: Default value from Attanasio, Banks, Meghir and Weber (JEBS, 1999).

gamma.title: Capital's share of output in firm production function
gamma.description: Capital's share of output in firm production function.
gamma.notes: Histroical value in U.S. is about 0.33, but Elsby, Hobijn, and Sahin (BPEA, 2013) find capital's share is increasing, so default value is above this.

epsilon.title: Elasticity of substitution between capital and labor in firm production function
epsilon.description: Elasticity of substitution between capital and labor in firm production function.
epsilon.notes: If epsilon=1, then production function is Cobb-Douglas.  If epsilon=0, then production function is perfect substitutes.

Z.title: Total factor productivity in firm production function
Z.description: Total factor productivity in firm production function.  Set value for base year, click '+' to add value for next year.  All future years not specified are set to last value entered.

delta_annual.title: Annual rate of economic depreciation of capital
delta_annual.description: Annual rate of economic depreciation of capital.
delta_annual.notes: Approximately the value from Kehoe calibration exercise: http://www.econ.umn.edu/~tkehoe/classes/calibration-04.pdf.

ltilde.title: Total time endowment of household
ltilde.notes: Can be normalized to 1.0 without loss of generality.

world_int_rate_annual.title: Exogenous annual world interest rate to be used when modeling a small open economy
world_int_rate_annual.description: Exogenous annual world interest rate to be used when modeling a small open economy. Set value for base year, click '+' to add value for next year.  All future years not specified are set to last value entered.

initial_foreign_debt_ratio.title: Share of government debt held by foreigners in model start year
initial_foreign_debt_ratio.description: Share of government debt held by foreigners in model start year.

zeta_D.title: Share of new debt issues from government that are purchased by foreigners
zeta_D.description: Share of new debt issues from government that are purchased by foreigners. Set value for base year, click '+' to add value for next year.  All future years not specified are set to last value entered.
zeta_D.notes: This value is about 0.4 historically for the U.S., set to zero to have closed econ as default.

zeta_K.title: Share of excess demand for capital that is supplied by foreigners
zeta_K.description: Share of excess demand for capital that is supplied by foreigners. Set value for base year, click '+' to add value for next year.  All future years not specified are set to last value entered.
zeta_K.notes: Set to 0.1 when running large-open verion of US economy, but hard to find data to pin this down.

tG1.title: Number of model periods until budget closure rule kicks in
tG1.description: Number of model periods until budget closure rule kicks in.
tG1.notes: It may make sense for this tG1 to exceed the length of the budget window one is looking at.  But it must also not be too late into the time path that a steady-state won't be reached by time T.

tG2.title: Number of model periods until budget closure ends and budgetary variables jump to steady-state values
tG2.description: Number of model periods until budget closure ends and budgetary variables jump to steady-state values.
tG2.notes: The number of periods until the closure rule ends must not exceed T, the time at which the model is assumed to reach the steady-state.

alpha_T.title: Exogenous ratio of government transfers to GDP when budget balance is false
alpha_T.description: Exogenous ratio of government transfers to GDP when budget balance is false. Set value for base year, click '+' to add value for next year.  All future years not specified are set to last value entered.

alpha_G.title: Exogenous ratio of government spending to GDP when budget balance is false
alpha_G.description: Exogenous ratio of government spending to GDP when budget balance is false. Set value for base year, click '+' to add value for next year.  All future years not specified are set to last value entered.

rho_G.title: Speed of convergence to a stable government budget deficit for periods [tG1, tG2-1]
rho_G.description: Speed of convergence to a stable government budget deficit for periods [tG1, tG2-1].

debt_ratio_ss.title: Debt to GDP ratio to be achieved in the steady state
debt_ratio_ss.description: Debt to GDP ratio to be achieved in the steady state.
debt_ratio_ss.notes: Note that depending upon the tax policy parameters, some debt to GDP ratios may not be achievable with positive government spending.

initial_debt_ratio.title: Debt to GDP ratio in the initial period
initial_debt_ratio.description: Debt to GDP ratio in the initial period.
initial_debt_ratio.notes: Should be calibrated based on government debt held by the public to GDP in the model start year.

r_gov_scale.title: Scale parameter to determine government interest rate
r_gov_scale.description: Parameter to scale the market interest rate to find interest rate on government debt.

r_gov_shift.title: Shift parameter to determine government interest rate
r_gov_shift.description: Parameter to shift the market interest rate to find interest rate on government debt.

cit_rate.title: Corporate income tax rate
cit_rate.description: Corporate income tax rate.  Set value for base year, click '+' to add value for next year.  All future years not specified are set to last value entered.
cit_rate.notes: This is the top marginal corporate income tax rate.

tau_c.title: Consumption tax rate
tau_c.description: Consumption tax rate.  Set value for base year, click '+' to add value for next year.  All future years not specified are set to last value entered.
tau_c.notes: This policy parameter represents the effective consumption tax rate from sales taxes, VATs, and excise taxes.  To capture exemptions of certain goods, this is assumed to vary by age and ability type.  It is thus a SxJ matrix.

delta_tau_annual.title: Annual rate of depreciation of capital for tax purposes
delta_tau_annual.description: Annual rate of depreciation of capital for tax purposes.  Set value for base year, click '+' to add value for next year.  All future years not specified are set to last value entered.
delta_tau_annual.notes: Cost-of-Capital-Calculator can help to calibrate this parameter.

h_wealth.title: Numerator in wealth tax function
h_wealth.description: Numerator in wealth tax function. Set value for base year, click '+' to add value for next year.  All future years not specified are set to last value entered.

m_wealth.title: Term in denominator in wealth tax function
m_wealth.description: Term in denominator in wealth tax function. Set value for base year, click '+' to add value for next year.  All future years not specified are set to last value entered.

p_wealth.title: Scale parameter in wealth tax function
p_wealth.description: Scale parameter in wealth tax function. Set value for base year, click '+' to add value for next year.  All future years not specified are set to last value entered.
p_wealth.notes: Set to 0 to have no wealth tax.

tau_bq.title: Linear tax rate on bequests
tau_bq.description: Linear tax rate on bequests. Set value for base year, click '+' to add value for next year.  All future years not specified are set to last value entered.

tau_payroll.title: Linear payroll tax rate
tau_payroll.description: Linear payroll tax rate. Set value for base year, click '+' to add value for next year.  All future years not specified are set to last value entered.
tau_payroll.notes: Set to zero as default since tax functions include income and payroll taxes.

eta.title: Government transfer allocation
eta.description: Matrix that allocated government transfers across households.
eta.notes: This SxJ matrix gives the fraction of total aggregate transfers going to each age s and ability type j.

zeta.title: Bequest distribution process
zeta.description: Matrix that describes the bequest distribution process.
zeta.notes: This SxJ matrix gives the fraction of total aggregate bequests going to each age s and ability type j.

use_zeta.title: Indicator variable for whether or not to use the zeta matrix to distribute bequests
use_zeta.description: Indicator variable for whether or not to use the zeta matrix to distribute bequests.

chi_n_80.title: Utility weight on disutility of labor supply
chi_n_80.description: Household utility weight on on disutility of labor supply.

constant_rates.title: Flag to use linear tax functions
constant_rates.description: Flag to use linear tax functions.

zero_taxes.title: Flag to run model without any individual income taxes
zero_taxes.description: Flag to run model without any individual income taxes.

analytical_mtrs.title: Flag to use analytically derived marginal tax rates in tax functions
analytical_mtrs.description: Flag to use analytically derived marginal tax rates in tax functions.

age_specific.title: Flag to use analytically derived marginal tax rates in tax functions
age_specific.description: Flag to use analytically derived marginal tax rates in tax functions.

retirement_age.title: Age at which agents can collect Social Security benefits
retirement_age.description: Age at which agents can collect Social Security benefits. Set value for base year, click '+' to add value for next year.  All future years not specified are set to last value entered.

AIME_num_years.title: Number of years used to compute average index monthly earnings (AIME)
AIME_num_years.description: Number of years used to compute average index monthly earnings (AIME).
AIME_num_years.notes: AIME is computed using average earnings from the highest earnings years for the number of years specified here.

AIME_bkt_1.title: Upper bound to the first average index monthly earnings (AIME) bracket
AIME_bkt_1.description: Upper bound to the first average index monthly earnings (AIME) bracket.

AIME_bkt_2.title: Upper bound to the second average index monthly earnings (AIME) bracket
AIME_bkt_2.description: Upper bound to the second average index monthly earnings (AIME) bracket.

PIA_rate_bkt_1.title: The rate used to determine the primary insurance amount (PIA) in the first bracket for average index monthly earnings (AIME)
PIA_rate_bkt_1.description: The rate used to determine the primary insurance amount (PIA) in the first bracket for average index monthly earnings (AIME).

PIA_rate_bkt_2.title: The rate used to determine the primary insurance amount (PIA) in the second bracket for average index monthly earnings (AIME)
PIA_rate_bkt_2.description: The rate used to determine the primary insurance amount (PIA) in the second bracket for average index monthly earnings (AIME).

PIA_rate_bkt_3.title: The rate used to determine the primary insurance amount (PIA) in the third bracket for average index monthly earnings (AIME)
PIA_rate_bkt_3.description: The rate used to determine the primary insurance amount (PIA) in the third bracket for average index monthly earnings (AIME).

PIA_maxpayment.title: The maximum primary insurance amount (PIA) payment
PIA_maxpayment.description: The maximum primary insurance amount (PIA) payment.

PIA_minpayment.title: The minimum primary insurance amount (PIA) payment
PIA_minpayment.description: The minimum primary insurance amount (PIA) payment.

replacement_rate_adjust.title: Adjustment to the Social Security retirement benefits replacement rate
replacement_rate_adjust.description: Adjustment to the Social Security retirement benefits replacement rate. Set value for base year, click '+' to add value for next year.  All future years not specified are set to last value entered.
replacement_rate_adjust.notes: This parameter willy only vary along the time path.  It is assumed to be one in the steady state.  The steady state retirement rate can be adjusted by changing the parameters of the retirement benefits function.

budget_balance.title: Flag to balance government budget in each period
budget_balance.description: Flag to balance government budget in each period.

baseline_spending.title: Flag to keep level of government spending and transfers constant between baseline and reform runs
baseline_spending.description: Flag to keep level of government spending and transfers constant between baseline and reform runs.

start_year.title: Calendar year in which to start model analysis
start_year.description: Calendar year in which to start model analysis.

tax_func_type.title: Functional form for individual income tax functions
tax_func_type.description: Functional form for individual income tax functions.

initial_guess_r_SS.title: Initial guess of r for the SS solution
initial_guess_r_SS.description: Initial guess of r for the SS solution.

initial_guess_TR_SS.title: Initial guess of TR for the SS solution
initial_guess_TR_SS.description: Initial guess of TR for the SS solution.

initial_guess_factor_SS.title: Initial guess of factor for the SS solution
initial_guess_factor_SS.description: Initial guess of factor for the SS solution.

omega.title: Population distribution (fraction at each age) over the time path.
omega.description: Population distribution (fraction at each age) over the time path.

omega_SS.title: Population distribution (fraction at each age) in the steady-state.
omega_SS.description: Population distribution (fraction at each age) in the steady-state.

omega_S_preTP.title: Population distribution (fraction at each age) in the period before the transition path begins.
omega_S_preTP.description: Population distribution (fraction at each age) in the period before the transition path begins.

g_n.title: Population growth rate over the time path.
g_n.description: Population growth rate over the time path.

g_n_ss.title: Population growth rate in the steady-state.
g_n_ss.description: Population growth rate in the steady-state.

imm_rates.title: Immigration rates over the time path.
imm_rates.description: Immigration rates over the time path.
